  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose is to characterize the change of respiratory admittance induced by salbutamol
      inhalation in children and young adults. A variation threshold will be fixed to distinguish
      asthmatic and healthy subjects.

      This project could allow a better identification of asthmatic individuals needing a
      treatment, a reduction of morbidity of asthma, a reduction of unnecessary treatments
      administered in individuals with respiratory but not asthmatic symptoms, a better
      comprehension of bronchial hyperreactivity and its role in asthmatic disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
